      "justification_correct": "Per CFE Manual and Beneish research, increasing DSRI suggests revenue recognition problems or fictitious sales, while increasing GMI indicates deteriorating margins possibly masked by manipulation. Combined elevation of these indices strongly correlates with earnings manipulation probability, contributing positively to M-Score values exceeding the -2.22 fraud threshold for financial statement fraud detection.",
      "justification_wrong": "Decreasing AQI indicates improving asset quality (less fraud risk). Decreasing DEPI and SGAI suggest conservative accounting practices. Increasing LVGI with decreasing TATA presents mixed signals. The DSRI-GMI combination specifically targets revenue manipulation patterns most associated with financial statement fraud per empirical research.",
