      "correct": 0,
      "justification_correct": "The Beneish M-Score uses -2.22 as the threshold. Scores above -2.22 suggest higher likelihood of manipulation, while scores below indicate lower probability. A score of -1.89 is above the threshold, but the question tests understanding that lower numerical values (more negative) indicate less manipulation likelihood per the CFE Manual's financial statement fraud detection methodologies.",
      "justification_wrong": "Misinterpretation of the M-Score threshold direction. Scores more negative than -2.22 suggest lower manipulation probability. The M-Score is a probabilistic indicator, not definitive proof requiring immediate reporting. All eight variables are standardized in the model and do not require recalculation based on examiner discretion per established methodology.",
      "difficulty": "EASY",
      "legacy": true,
      "legacy_source": "financial_transactions/quiz_001_en.json"
    },
    {
      "num": 6,
      "text": "A company's Asset Quality Index (AQI) increased from 1.0 to 1.42, while the Depreciation Index (DEPI) rose to 1.35. Total accruals to total assets ratio increased to 8.2%. According to the Beneish M-Score framework, what is the aggregate fraud probability assessment?",
      "tag": "Beneish M-Score",
      "options": [
        "D. Indeterminate—M-Score cannot be calculated without complete financial ratios",
