      ],
      "correct": 3,
      "justification_correct": "CFE Manual 2024 specifies AQI >1.3 suggests decreased asset quality through capitalization of expenses; DEPI >1.0 indicates slowing depreciation to inflate earnings; total accruals >6% signals aggressive accrual manipulation. Multiple elevated indices simultaneously substantially increase financial statement fraud probability, warranting comprehensive investigation per Beneish methodology.",
      "justification_wrong": "These indices significantly exceed CFE-established thresholds for manipulation indicators. The simultaneous elevation of asset quality deterioration, depreciation manipulation, and excessive accruals creates compounding fraud risk. Industry benchmarking does not override multiple threshold breaches, and sufficient data exists for M-Score probability assessment.",
